node.text:
Sunday Grandstand 
 
After the Goodwood Festival of Speed a couple of weeks back we headed to the Goodwood Motor Circuit with the Oxford Commission, a Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer - representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. 
 
A few friends showed up and the rain held off. So we made a film. 
 
We hope you like it. 
Sound 👆  
 
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study embody the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence. 
 
Film @thisisgrip 
Driving: @mfranchitti 
Location: @goodwoodmotorcircuit 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #oxford #sundayvibes

node.text:
Over the last 4 days, the first 2 client-specification cars representing the results of the Dynamics and a Lightweighting Study (DLS) have been running at Goodwood Festival of Speed. 
 
Unico is presented in Absinthe Green over Blood Orange, with Nickel polished brightwork. 
 
Oxford is presented in Oak Green Metallic over Bone White, with Champagne polished trim. 
 
Both DLS cars are powered by the 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat six, developed in collaboration with Williams Advanced Engineering - producing 500 HP. 
 
🎥 @thisisgrip 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #FOS #greenmachines

node.text:
For Singer Sunday, here’s a look at the visit of these Porsche 911s reimagined by Singer to Frankfurt.

Representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study, the machine in Parallax White was accompanied by the Monaco Commission, in Midnight Blue Metallic.

This fantastic set-up was created by the awesome team @doerrgroup, who support Singer’s clients in Germany as members of our global partner network

#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #frankfurt

node.text:
It’s Monday, so here’s a look back at our Singer Ten Years celebrations at Monterey Car Week in August.

Our aim was not just to assemble some beautiful cars but to create a program that would enable them to be driven and enjoyed.

We began with a drive from Singer HQ near Los Angeles north to Monterey. Behind the wheel were a group of Singer clients, friends and team members. The cars were a chorus of Porsche 911s Reimagined by Singer and assorted sports machines
We took the road less travelled.

Once in Monterey it was a non-stop week taking in:

McCalls Motorworks Revival 
The Dynamics and Lightweighting Study was presented with our friends at @Hagerty

The annual Singer House party 
Invited guests enjoyed the cars (and actual horse power) on display, accompanied by incredible food from the @MichelinGuide chefs.

The Quail, A Motorsports Gathering 
Singer presented five cars from the last ten years, ranging from the first G-series cars, the first 964 restoration, the rise of the Targa and the development of Singer’s Special Wishes services and onto the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. 
Werks Reunion, Monterey
Along with our friends @michelinusa we presented 3 restorations showing what happens when the Singer philosophy #EverythingisImportant meets the @michelin #DevotiontoDetail approach.

Historics, Big Sur, Pebble Beach
After a visit to the Monterey Motorsports Reunion at Laguna Seca, our Singer Experience group took their cars south for another great drive in northern California. The weekend then moved to the famous Pebble Beach concours lawn.

Laguna Seca
The week came to a close on Monday with a private track day. As the track closed, we filled the start - finish straight with air-cooled Porsches for a final technicolour group photograph.

Enormous thanks to everyone who joined us for the experience or came to talk cars and watches with us.
A salute to all the team - both those at Singer base and those on location in Monterey who made this whole operation a success.

Film by @zackj_com

#singertenyears #singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #handcrafted #everythingisimportant #mondaymotivation

node.text:
Yesterday we wrapped up our 10th Anniversary trip to Monterey Car Week with a track day at the WeatherTech Raceway Laguna Seca.

Our Singer Experience clients had the track to themselves with technical support from our friends @michelinusa and ran hard all day. The Porsche 911s Reimagined by Singer were joined by a few friends as you’ll see from the film... Our thanks to all our clients for their support over the last decade, all the Singer team in Monterey, Los Angeles, the UK and Geneva who worked to put this week together. 
Likewise we’re grateful for the support of all our amazing partners and everyone who came to see us and talk cars and watches during the last week.

Thanks to @zackj_com and @drewphillipsphoto for the awesome films and images.

#singertenyears #singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #handcrafted #everythingisimportant #montereycarweek #devotiontodetail #michelin

node.text:
Yesterday, Singer’s Car Week continued with The Quail, A Motorsport Gathering. 
The team worked through the night to set-up a display at this wonderful event, representing the evolution of the Singer philosophy over 10 years, from a G-series restoration, the first 964 restoration, a 4WD Targa, a Special Wishes car and then on to the Dynamics & Lightweighting Study.

Simultaneously a further 3 cars were at Werks Reunion with our friends @michelinusa as part of our ongoing #carweek celebrations for our 10th anniversary.

Here’s a look at the day in Monterey.

#singertenyears #singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #handcrafted #everythingisimportant #montereycarweek #devotiontodetail #michelin

node.text:
Dynamics and Lightweighting Study details.  
  
Lightweight, magnesium, centre-lock wheels.  
 
Ram-air intakes feeding the 500 HP, 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat six.  
  
Rear compartment cross-brace. 
  
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study embody the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence.  
  
📷  @actcreative  
  
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #oxford

Sunday Grandstand 
 
After the Goodwood Festival of Speed a couple of weeks back we headed to the Goodwood Motor Circuit with the Oxford Commission, a Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer - representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study. 
 
A few friends showed up and the rain held off. So we made a film. 
 
We hope you like it. 
Sound 👆  
 
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study embody the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence. 
 
Film @thisisgrip 
Driving: @mfranchitti 
Location: @goodwoodmotorcircuit 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #oxford #sundayvibes

node.text:
The Oxford commission is a Porsche 911 reimagined by Singer, representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study, undertaken on behalf of our clients.  
  
An insight into some of the specification details is as follows:  
  
This machine is specified with an interior in Bone White, with bespoke Tartan seat centres.  
The dashboard is specified in visible carbon, as is the gear shifter - which also features a maple wood insert.  
The tachometer is presented in 18ct gold and the Everything is Important motif is selected for the door sill plates.  
  
The aero-optimised, carbon-fibre bodywork is presented in Oak Green Metallic with Champagne polished bright trim.  
  
To see (and hear) this machine in action, stay-tuned.  
  
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study embody the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence.  
  
📷  @actcreative  
Location: @bicesterheritage  
  
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #oxford #fridayfeeling

node.text:
The Unico Commission, representing the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study, photographed @bicesterheritage  
 
This Porsche 911 is restored and reimagined by Singer in the U.K. and is presented with carbon fibre, aero-optimised bodywork in Absinthe Green. Light-ghosted stripes are combined with lettering in Blood Orange. 
 
Inside, bespoke, lightweight carbon-fibre seats are trimmed in Blood Orange with nickel grommets.  
 
This machine is powered by a 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat-six - producing 500 HP at 9000 rpm. 
 
📷 by @actcreative 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS

node.text:
After the awesome 2021 @fosgoodwood, Singer headed to the iconic @goodwoodmotorcircuit last week. 
 
We brought the first client-specification Dynamics and Lightweighting Study (DLS) restorations - shownn here is the Oxford commission in Oak Green Metallic. 
 
@mfranchitti was behind the wheel, wearing the prototype @singerreimagined Track 1 chronograph, thanks to our friends @phillipsperpetual. 
 
Look out for our film of the car on track coming soon. 
 
Images by @actcreative 
Huge thanks to the team at Goodwood Motor Circuit for looking after us so well. 
 
Combining iconic design with cutting-edge engineering and material science, both Track 1 and the results of the Dynamics and Lightweighting Study personify the Singer philosophy - A Relentless Pursuit of Excellence. 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #greenmachines #chronograph

node.text:
Over the last 4 days, the first 2 client-specification cars representing the results of the Dynamics and a Lightweighting Study (DLS) have been running at Goodwood Festival of Speed. 
 
Unico is presented in Absinthe Green over Blood Orange, with Nickel polished brightwork. 
 
Oxford is presented in Oak Green Metallic over Bone White, with Champagne polished trim. 
 
Both DLS cars are powered by the 4.0L, 4-valves per cylinder, naturally aspirated, air-cooled flat six, developed in collaboration with Williams Advanced Engineering - producing 500 HP. 
 
🎥 @thisisgrip 
 
#singervehicledesign #singerreimagined #porsche #porsche911 #porschemoment #everythingisimportant #DLS #FOS #greenmachines
